<L>__{exterior streetside cafe, little italy. day.}
<C>__{truman}
<P>__{(to the jogger with the familiar sneakers)}
<D>__{small world.}
<C>__{jogger 1}
<P>__{(attempting to sidestep truman)}
<D>__{excuse me.}
<A>__{truman blocks the man a second time.}
<C>__{truman}
<D>__{you don't remember? two days ago i gave you my meatball sandwich in the park. you were in a wheelchair. same sneakers.}
<A>__{an almost subliminal flashback appears in truman's head confirming that the jogger and the homeless man in the wheelchair two days earlier are one and the same.}
<C>__{truman}
<P>__{(commenting ironically on his new found mobility)}
<D>__{a miracle!}
<C>__{jogger 2}
<P>__{(coming to his companion's aid)}
<D>__{get the hell outta here.}
<A>__{the second jogger pushes truman back against the cafe table causing him to stumble.}
